AVIAN INFLUENZA (49): MONGOLIA (ARKHANGAI) WILD BIRDS, H5
*********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Tue 11 Aug 2009
Source: Xinhua News Agency [in Chinese, trans. & summ. Rappt.DS, edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/tech/2009-08/11/content_11863783.htm>


An official with Mongolia's Emergency Situations Ministry has confirmed to
Xinhua on 11 Aug 2009 that avian influenza recently occurred in Arkhangai
Province.

Mongolian disease control and prevention agencies found 56 dead swans, wild
geese, and other kinds of birds in the area around Shelechagan
[transliteration] Lake in Tsetserleg District of Arkhangai Province and
after testing samples, confirmed that the birds had died of avian influenza
virus. For the moment, it has been confirmed that the virus is H5 subtype.

[byline: A Sigang]

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail rapporteur Dan Silver

[According to an immediate notification of the Mongolian authorities to the
OIE, submitted on Mon 10 Aug 2009, the information above relates to an
outbreak of highly pathogenic avian influenza virus serotype H5, involving
56 dead wild birds of unspecified species. According to the newswire above,
however, swans and wild geese were among the birds affected. The outbreak
reportedly started on 1 Aug 2009 and was lab-confirmed by haemagglutination
(HA) test, nested RT-PCR and real-time PCR on 6 Aug 2009. The location is
indicated as 'Arkhangai (Doroo nuur, Tsetserleg soum)'. For the
notification, including a map, see
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/reports/en_imm_0000008354_20090810_170618.pdf>. -
Mod.AS

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Mongolia is available at
<http://healthmap.org/r/00FQ> and an administrative map at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/mongolia_pol96.jpg>. -
Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
